A block A of mass m kg lies on block B of mass m kg. B in turn lies on smooth horizontal plane. The coefficient of friction between A and B is m. Both the blocks are initially at rest. A horizontal force F is applied to lower block B at t = 0 such that there is relative motion between A and B. Column I

Column II

The displacement of A shall be less than displacement L of  block B.

And the work done by friction on block B is negative and its magnitude is equal to mmgL.

Therefore workdone by friction on block A plus on block B is negative  its magnitude is less than mmgL.

Work done by F is positive. Since F> 2mmg, magnitude of work done by F shall be more than  mmgL.
